	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=4778&amp;mid=103357017332122">Clarification on regen</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=4778&amp;mid=103357017332122#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Wed, Oct 2nd 11:06 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=112394"><span id=" ">jvickers</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">5 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>I've seen a lot of regen rates posted here for this item, ranging from 3hp to 12hp per tick, with the most common being 5hp/tick.<br/><br/>This item adds 5hp per tick and as far as I know is not level dependent (I'm level 60 and haven't tried it at other levels).<br/><br/>The reason some of you think that it adds 12hp/tick or is level dependent is that your *base* regen rate is level dependent.<br/><br/>A non iksar/troll, sitting, at level 60 regens 7 per tick.&nbsp;&nbsp;This item adds 5 to that for a *total* of 12.<br/><br/>I'm a 60 mage with 3aa in regen.  I get 20 per tick while sitting with this item and with my self buff up:  7 base (for being lvl 60), + 3aa + 5 for my tpp buff, +5 for the heart.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
